{% if isTooLatePage %}
<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

  <h3>How late can I plant {{ pageData.cropName }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}?</h3>
  <p>
    {% if pageData.copy.safeDateLong and pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong and pageData.copy.safeDateLong == pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong %}
      Most gardeners use about {{ pageData.copy.safeDateLong }} as the late planting cutoff from local averages.
    {% elif pageData.copy.safeDateLong and pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong %}
      Most gardeners aim to plant by about {{ pageData.copy.safeDateLong }}, but planting can still be reasonable until around {{ pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong }} if variety choice, timing, and early growth are all helping.
    {% elif pageData.copy.safeDateLong %}
      Most gardeners aim to plant by about {{ pageData.copy.safeDateLong }}. After that, the fit usually gets noticeably tighter.
    {% elif pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong %}
      There is not much comfortable late window from local averages, but planting can still be realistic until around {{ pageData.copy.borderlineDateLong }} in the better cases.
    {% else %}
      {{ pageData.cropName }} is usually beyond the comfortable late planting window in {{ pageData.cityName }} when gardeners are relying on average local conditions alone.
    {% endif %}
  </p>

  <h3>What matters most if I am planting {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} late?</h3>
  <p>
    The biggest things are how much season is still left, how fast the variety matures, and how cleanly the crop gets started. Once the normal window closes, small delays and weak early growth matter more than they did earlier.
  </p>

  <h3>Can a faster variety still make late planting realistic?</h3>
  <p>
    {% if fastestVarietyDisplay %}
      Often yes. In this climate, {{ fastestVarietyDisplay.nounPhrasePlural }} usually leave the most room when planting is delayed.
    {% else %}
      Often yes. Faster-maturing varieties usually give the best remaining chance when planting is delayed.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</section>

