{% if isMaturityPage %}
<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

  <h3>Will {{ pageData.cropName }} usually mature before frost in {{ pageData.cityName }}?</h3>
  <p>
    {% if pageData.copy.fitRank >= 3 %}
      Usually yes. {{ pageData.copy.timingSummary }}
    {% elif pageData.copy.fitRank == 2 %}
      Usually yes, but with less room for delay or slower variety choice. {{ pageData.copy.timingSummary }}
    {% elif pageData.copy.fitRank == 1 %}
      Sometimes, but timing and variety choice matter much more here. {{ pageData.copy.timingSummary }}
    {% else %}
      Usually not without help from faster varieties, stronger starts, or a better setup. {{ pageData.copy.timingSummary }}
    {% endif %}
  </p>

  <h3>What usually decides whether {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} finishes in time?</h3>
  <p>
    The biggest factors are the normal planting date, how much heat the crop needs, the local fall frost timing, and whether the chosen variety is on the faster or slower end of the local range.
  </p>

  <h3>Which varieties usually give the best chance of maturing?</h3>
  <p>
    {% if fastestVarietyDisplay %}
      In this climate, {{ fastestVarietyDisplay.nounPhrasePlural }} usually leave the most room.
    {% else %}
      The best chance usually comes from the faster end of the maturity range for this crop.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</section>

